      "rationale": "Numerical code verification at MRL 5 requires demonstration that the solver correctly implements the governing equations. Method of Manufactured Solutions (MMS) was applied to the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver, confirming second-order spatial convergence (observed order p=1.97 vs. theoretical p=2.0) and first-order temporal convergence for the transient solver. Benchmark comparisons against three analytical solutions (Poiseuille flow, Taylor-Couette flow, lid-driven cavity at Re=400) all within 0.1% of analytical values. Achieved Gradation 5 exceeds requirement.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-mrl5-ac-ncv",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical code verification acceptance criteria — MRL 5",
