      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty assessed at highest rigor for MRL 5. Turbulence model selection: k-ω SST evaluated against k-ε realizable and LES on a representative impeller passage; k-ω SST selected based on superior agreement with PIV data (WSS error 8.1% vs. 14.3% for k-ε). Hemolysis damage model: Giersiepen-Wurzinger power law validated against Heuser-Opitz data; model form uncertainty quantified via interval analysis on exponents α and β. Newtonian blood assumption justified: Womersley number Wo=0.8 and shear rates > 100 s⁻¹ throughout pump domain confirm negligible non-Newtonian effects. All model form assumptions documented, justified, and sensitivity-tested. Achieved Gradation 5.",
