    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for the CFD hemolysis prediction model at MRL 5 is accepted based on the following structured evidence: (1) All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed and all achievedLevels meet or exceed requiredLevels. No shortfalls exist. (2) The primary QoI (NIH) prediction error is 6.3% mean absolute relative error across 5 operating points, with validation metric |E| ≤ 0.72 at all points — well within the acceptance criterion of |E| ≤ 1.0. (3) Total expanded uncertainty on NIH prediction is ±14.2% (k=2), dominated by damage model coefficient uncertainty (Sobol S₁=0.41) and rotational speed uncertainty (S₁=0.28), both of which are characterized and bounded within the operating envelope. (4) Numerical errors are fully characterized: discretization error 2.1%, solver convergence error < 0.1%, code verification confirmed by MMS to second-order accuracy. (5) Software quality assurance and use error controls are commensurate with MRL 5, including independent peer review, automated quality checks, and version-controlled configuration. (6) Validation activities are directly relevant to the COU: same geometry, overlapping operating conditions, and matched dimensionless parameters. (7) The sensitivity analysis (N=4096 Sobol) confirms no uncharacterized dominant uncertainty sources. The model is fit for the intended purpose of predicting absolute hemolysis levels for regulatory submission of a Class II CPB device.",
